Ham-WorldMap

Creates an Imager image containing an equirectangular projection of the world map, with optional
Maidenhead locator grid and day/night illumination showing the area of enhanced propagation known as the 'grey line'.
Also utility methods for adding dots at locator positions or lat/long coords, and filling grid squares with colour
to provide a 'heat map' of activity from these squares.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Ham::WorldMap

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Ham-WorldMap

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Ham-WorldMap

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Ham-WorldMap

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Ham-WorldMap/


EXAMPLE CODE

Please see my gridmapper code, at https://bitbucket.org/devzendo/gridmapper
This draws maps based on logged data from WSJT-X and from .adif files.

